\subsection{Bézout module of a hypergeometric motive}
\begin{definition}\label{hgm.bezout_module}
\uses{hgm.bezout_matrix,hgm.degree}
The **Bezout module** of a hypergeometric motive $M$ is the finite $\mathbb{Z}$-module whose relations matrix is the {{ KNOWL('hgm.bezout_matrix', 'Bézout matrix') }} $B$ of $M$. In other words, it is the quotient $\mathbb{Z}^d/B \mathbb{Z}^d$, where $d$ is the {{ KNOWL('hgm.degree', 'degree') }} of $M$.
\end{definition}


